 Dispatches is a British television current affairs documentary series on      
 Channel 4, first transmitted in 1987. The programme covers issues about       
 British society, politics, health, religion, international current affairs and
 the environment.                                                              
                                                                               
 Jon Snow reports on general practitioners who have been responsible for 
 repeated misdiagnoses, but have been allowed to continue practising. He
 highlights how, six years after the Shipman Inquiry called for increased 
 scrutiny to be placed on doctors, GPs who have been sanctioned by the
 authorities in the past are seldom assessed, and hears from a whistleblowing
 doctor and nurse who reveal flaws in the way patients are alerted to cases 
 of malpractice.
